Source:
  Title: A Year with Hafiz
  Translator: Daniel Ladinsky
  Author: Hafiz
  ISBN: 978-0143117544
  Publisher: Penguin Books
Format: Verse
By: Hafiz
Title: I Had a Legitimate Excuse
Description: April 3
---
I had a legitimate excuse for not going to the mosque and temple to
pray.

It was because love is so wild in me I might break the fragile glass
cage that all religions are made of.
